@pmeier I believe the `init_weights` and `dropout` parameters are unintentionally missed here. This issue is caused because we didn't follow the normal idiom for `Inception3`. Here is how `GoogLeNet` does it:
https://github.com/pytorch/vision/blob/a89b1957a62e2f68f001d5d60268743edbe164d8/torchvision/models/quantization/googlenet.py#L76-L79


Normally we grab args and kwargs, overwrite the things we want and pass them to the super constructor. IMO `QuantizableInception3` should do exactly the same. Instead of trying to redefine all the parameters with the same defaults, we should just do the redirection.

